Directions

Preparation:25min  ›  Cook:30min  ›  Ready in:55min 
Preheat oven to 180 degrees C. Grease and flour a 20cm square baking tin.
In a large saucepan, melt butter. Remove from heat and stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla essence.
Beat in cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder. Spread mixture into prepared tin.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not overcook.
Icing: Combine together in a bowl, butter, cocoa, honey, vanilla essence and icing sugar until smooth. Ice brownies while they are still warm. When cool cut into 16 squares